label: Public Safety Artifact Function

definition_enriched: Public Safety Artifact Function is a Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes of preventing and responding to events that could endanger the safety of the general public from significant danger, injury/harm, or damage, such as crimes or disasters (natural or man-made).

label: Pulsejet Engine
definition_original: An Air-Breathing Jet Engine that is capable of operating statically and uses intermittent (pulsing) Combustion of the fuel-oxidizer mixture before expelling the exhaust out through the rear Propelling Nozzle to generate Thrust.
definition_enriched: Pulsejet Engine is an Air-Breathing Jet Engine that is capable of operating statically and uses intermittent (pulsing) Combustion of the fuel-oxidizer mixture before expelling the exhaust out through the rear Propelling Nozzle to generate Thrust.

definition_original: A Radio Communication Instrument that is an electronic device that is designed to extract information from radio waves intercepted by a Radio Antenna by using electronic filters to separate the desired radio frequency signal from other signals, an electronic amplifier to increase the power of the signal, and demodulation to recover the desired information.
definition_enriched: Radio Receiver is a Radio Communication Instrument that is an electronic device that is designed to extract information from radio waves intercepted by a Radio Antenna by using electronic filters to separate the desired radio frequency signal from other signals, an electronic amplifier to increase the power of the signal, and demodulation to recover the desired information.

definition_enriched: Radio Repeater is a Radio Transceiver that is designed to receive a radio signal, amplify it, and retransmit it (often on another frequency).

label: Random Wire Antenna

definition_enriched: Random Wire Antenna is a Wire Antenna that consists of a long wire suspended above the ground with a length that does not bear a relation to the wavelength of the radio waves used and which is typically used as a receiving antenna on the long, medium, and short wave bands.

label: Tank
definition_original: An Armored Fighting Vehicle that is designed to carry heavy firepower, have a powerful Engine, and travel on one or more continuous tracks such that it is suitable for front-line combat and can provide operational maneuverability as well as tactical offensive and defensive capabilities.
definition_enriched: Tank is an Armored Fighting Vehicle that is designed to carry heavy firepower, have a powerful Engine, and travel on one or more continuous tracks such that it is suitable for front-line combat and can provide operational maneuverability as well as tactical offensive and defensive capabilities.

label: Telecommunication Endpoint
definition_original: A Telecommunication Network Node that connects a Telecommunication Terminal to a Telecommunication Network.
definition_enriched: Telecommunication Endpoint is a Telecommunication Network Node that connects a Telecommunication Terminal to a Telecommunication Network.

label: Telecommunication Infrastructure
definition_original: An Infrastructure System that is designed to support the use of Telecommunication Instruments to communicate.
definition_enriched: Telecommunication Infrastructure is an Infrastructure System that is designed to support the use of Telecommunication Instruments to communicate.

label: Telecommunication Instrument
definition_original: A Communication Instrument that is designed for use by some Agent in some Act of Communication where the recipient of that communication is potentially a significant distance away from the Agent.
definition_enriched: Telecommunication Instrument is a Communication Instrument that is designed for use by some Agent in some Act of Communication where the recipient of that communication is potentially a significant distance away from the Agent.

label: Telecommunication Network
definition_original: A Communication System that is designed to enable the transmission of information over significant distances between Telecommunication Endpoints via Telecommunication Network Nodes and Lines.
definition_enriched: A Communication System that is designed to enable the transmission of information between telecommunication endpoints via interconnected network nodes and lines.

label: Telecommunication Network Line
definition_original: A Communication Artifact that is designed to be the physical transmission medium that connects two or more Telecommunication Network Nodes within a Telecommunication Network to facilitate communication between the Nodes.
definition_enriched: Telecommunication Network Line is a Communication Artifact that is designed to be the physical transmission medium that connects two or more Telecommunication Network Nodes within a Telecommunication Network to facilitate communication between the Nodes.

label: Telecommunication Network Node
definition_original: A Communication Artifact that consists of a connection point, redistribution point, or endpoint that is designed to be part of a Telecommunication Network and can be either active or passive.
definition_enriched: Telecommunication Network Node is a Communication Artifact that consists of a connection point, redistribution point, or endpoint that is designed to be part of a Telecommunication Network and can be either active or passive.

label: Telecommunication Switching Node
definition_original: A Telecommunication Network Node that is capable of redirecting a communication transmission to another Telecommunication Network Node.
definition_enriched: Telecommunication Switching Node is a Telecommunication Network Node that is capable of redirecting a communication transmission to another Telecommunication Network Node.

label: Telephone
definition_original: A Telecommunication Instrument that is designed to provide point-to-point communication between agents by means of audio messages.
definition_enriched: Telephone is a Telecommunication Instrument that is designed to provide point-to-point communication between agents by means of audio messages.

label: Telephone Line
definition_original: A Telecommunication Network Line that consists of a physical wire or other signaling medium that is designed to be part of a Telephone Network.
definition_enriched: Telephone Line is a Telecommunication Network Line that consists of a physical wire or other signaling medium that is designed to be part of a Telephone Network.

label: Telephone Network
definition_original: A Telecommunication Network that is designed to allow telephone calls to be made between two or more parties connected to the network.
definition_enriched: Telephone Network is a Telecommunication Network that is designed to allow telephone calls to be made between two or more parties connected to the network.

label: Telephone Subscriber Line
definition_original: A Telephone Line that connects a Communication Endpoint to another node in a Telecommunication Network to enable service to a user's Telephone.
definition_enriched: Telephone Subscriber Line is a Telephone Line that connects a Communication Endpoint to another node in a Telecommunication Network to enable service to a user's Telephone.

label: Telescope
definition_original: An Imaging Instrument that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing Electromagnetic Radiation to form an enhanced image of the Object.
definition_enriched: Telescope is an Imaging Instrument that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing Electromagnetic Radiation to form an enhanced image of the Object.

label: Temperature Measurement Artifact Function
definition_original: A Measurement Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to measure the Temperature of a specified object or class of objects.
definition_enriched: Temperature Measurement Artifact Function is a Measurement Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to measure the Temperature of a specified object or class of objects.

label: Terminal Board
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to join electrical terminations and create an electrical circuit by means of a block which connects individual wires without a splice or physically joining the ends.
definition_enriched: Terminal Board is a Material Artifact that is designed to join electrical terminations and create an electrical circuit by means of a block which connects individual wires without a splice or physically joining the ends.

label: Thermal Control Artifact Function
definition_original: An Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact increasing, decreasing, or maintaining the temperature of itself, a part of itself, or another object.
definition_enriched: Thermal Control Artifact Function is an Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact increasing, decreasing, or maintaining the temperature of itself, a part of itself, or another object.

label: Thermal Imaging Artifact Function
definition_original: An Imaging Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to create a visual representation of an entity using radiation from the far infrared region of the electromagnetic spectrum that the entity emits
definition_enriched: Thermal Imaging Artifact Function is an Imaging Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to create a visual representation of an entity using radiation from the far infrared region of the electromagnetic spectrum that the entity emits.

label: Thermal Insulation Artifact Function
definition_original: A Thermal Control Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact prevents or reduces the transfer of heat between objects that are in thermal contact or in range of radiative influence.
definition_enriched: Thermal Insulation Artifact Function is a Thermal Control Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact prevents or reduces the transfer of heat between objects that are in thermal contact or in range of radiative influence.

label: Timekeeping Artifact Function
definition_original: An Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to keep track of and report the current time.
definition_enriched: Timekeeping Artifact Function is an Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to keep track of and report the current time.

label: Title Document
definition_original: A Legal Instrument that is designed as evidence of ownership.
definition_enriched: Title Document is a Legal Instrument that is designed as evidence of ownership.

label: Tool
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to assist in the performance of manual or mechanical work and not to be consumed in that process.
definition_enriched: Tool is a Material Artifact that is designed to assist in the performance of manual or mechanical work and not to be consumed in that process.

label: Torpedo
definition_original: A Precision-Guided Missile that is designed to be fired into a body of water, be self-propelled through the water, and carry an explosive payload.
definition_enriched: Torpedo is a Precision-Guided Missile that is designed to be fired into a body of water, be self-propelled through the water, and carry an explosive payload.

label: Torpedo Tube
definition_original: A Projectile Launcher that is designed to launch Torpedoes.
definition_enriched: Torpedo Tube is a Projectile Launcher that is designed to launch Torpedoes.

label: Trail
definition_original: A Land Transportation Artifact that is designed to enable transport through rough country, such as a forest or moor.
definition_enriched: A Land Transportation Artifact that is designed to enable pedestrian or non-motorized travel through natural or constructed environments, including forests, moors, or urban greenways.

label: Train
definition_original: A Rail Transport Vehicle that consists of a series of connected Train Cars or Railcars.
definition_enriched: Train is a Rail Transport Vehicle that consists of a series of connected Train Cars or Railcars.

label: Train Car
definition_original: A Rail Transport Vehicle that consists of a single Vehicle that is not a Train but is designed to be connected to other Train Cars along with at least one Locomotive to form a Train.
definition_enriched: Train Car is a Rail Transport Vehicle that consists of a single Vehicle that is not a Train but is designed to be connected to other Train Cars along with at least one Locomotive to form a Train.

label: Transducer
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to convert one form of energy to another.
definition_enriched: Transducer is a Material Artifact that is designed to convert one form of energy to another.

label: Transportation Artifact
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is fixed in place and designed to enable the movement of Vehicles and Agents from one location to another.
definition_enriched: Transportation Artifact is a Material Artifact that is fixed in place and designed to enable the movement of Vehicles and Agents from one location to another.

label: Transportation Infrastructure
definition_original: An Infrastructure System that has continuant part one or more Transportation Artifacts and bears a function that, if realized, is realized in Acts of Cargo Transportation
definition_enriched: An Infrastructure System that has continuant part one or more Transportation Artifacts and bears a function that, if realized, is realized in acts of transportation of passengers and/or cargo.

label: Trim Tab
definition_original: A Control Surface that is designed to counteract hydro-, aerodynamic, or other forces in order to stabilize the Vehicle it is part of in the desired Attitude.
definition_enriched: Trim Tab is a Control Surface that is designed to counteract hydro-, aerodynamic, or other forces in order to stabilize the Vehicle it is part of in the desired Attitude.

label: Triple Inertial Navigation System
definition_original: An Inertial Navigation System that is designed to use three redundant computers to continuously calculate via dead reckoning the position, orientation, and velocity of a moving object without the need for external references, in such a way that eliminates the need for a navigator.
definition_enriched: Triple Inertial Navigation System is an Inertial Navigation System that is designed to use three redundant computers to continuously calculate via dead reckoning the position, orientation, and velocity of a moving object without the need for external references, in such a way that eliminates the need for a navigator.

label: Tripod
definition_original: A Material Artifact that consists of three legs and a platform that joins them and which is designed to support the weight and maintain the stability of objects that are attached to or rested on the platform.
definition_enriched: Tripod is a Material Artifact that consists of three legs and a platform that joins them and which is designed to support the weight and maintain the stability of objects that are attached to or rested on the platform.

label: Truck
definition_original: A Ground Motor Vehicle that is designed to be used to transport cargo.
definition_enriched: Truck is a Ground Motor Vehicle that is designed to be used to transport cargo.

label: Tunnel
definition_original: A Land Transportation Artifact that is designed to enable Ground Vehicles to travel underneath a surrounding soil, earth, or rock formation.
definition_enriched: A Land Transportation Artifact that is designed to enable ground vehicles to travel beneath surrounding soil, rock, or a water body (including riverbeds or seabeds).

label: Turbine Steam Engine
definition_original: A Steam Engine that is designed to extract thermal energy from pressurized steam and use it to do mechanical work on a rotating output shaft.
definition_enriched: Turbine Steam Engine is a Steam Engine that is designed to extract thermal energy from pressurized steam and use it to do mechanical work on a rotating output shaft.

label: Turbofan Air-Breathing Jet Engine
definition_original: An Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses a Turbofan, which consists of a Turbine and a Fan.
definition_enriched: Turbofan Air-Breathing Jet Engine is an Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses a Turbofan, which consists of a Turbine and a Fan.

label: Turbojet Air-Breathing Jet Engine
definition_original: An Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses a Turbojet, which consists of a Turbine with a Propelling Nozzle.
definition_enriched: Turbojet Air-Breathing Jet Engine is an Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses a Turbojet, which consists of a Turbine with a Propelling Nozzle.

label: Ultra High Frequency Communication Instrument
definition_original: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to participate in some process that has process part some Ultra High Frequency.
definition_enriched: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to transmit and/or receive radio signals in the ultra high frequency (UHF) band.

label: Ultraviolet Telescope
definition_original: A Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing ultraviolet light to form an enhanced image of the Object.
definition_enriched: Ultraviolet Telescope is a Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing ultraviolet light to form an enhanced image of the Object.

label: Unguided Rocket
definition_original: A Portion of Ammunition that is designed to be a self-propelled, but unguided, projectile that delivers some payload (explosive or other) over relatively long distances through the use of a Rocket Engine.
definition_enriched: Unguided Rocket is a Portion of Ammunition that is designed to be a self-propelled, but unguided, projectile that delivers some payload (explosive or other) over relatively long distances through the use of a Rocket Engine.

label: Valve
definition_original: A Fluid Control Artifact that is designed to regulate, direct, or control the flow of fluid by opening, closing, or partially obstructing the fluid from moving along a passageway.
definition_enriched: Valve is a Fluid Control Artifact that is designed to regulate, direct, or control the flow of fluid by opening, closing, or partially obstructing the fluid from moving along a passageway.

label: Vehicle
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to facilitate the movement of material entities from one location to another by conveying them there.
definition_enriched: Vehicle is a Material Artifact that is designed to facilitate the movement of material entities from one location to another by conveying them there.

label: Vehicle Compartment
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to partition a Vehicle into subdivisions for various purposes.
definition_enriched: Vehicle Compartment is a Material Artifact that is designed to partition a Vehicle into subdivisions for various purposes.

label: Vehicle Control System
definition_original: A Control System that is designed to enable some Agent to control some Vehicle.
definition_enriched: Vehicle Control System is a Control System that is designed to enable some Agent to control some Vehicle.

label: Vehicle Frame
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to be the main supporting structure of some Vehicle.
definition_enriched: Vehicle Frame is a Material Artifact that is designed to be the main supporting structure of some Vehicle.

label: Vehicle Track
definition_original: An Object Track for a Vehicle during some motion.
definition_enriched: Vehicle Track is an Object Track for a Vehicle during some motion.

label: Vehicle Track Point
definition_original: An Object Track Point that is where a Vehicle is or was located during some motion.
definition_enriched: Vehicle Track Point is an Object Track Point that is where a Vehicle is or was located during some motion.

label: Vehicle Transmission
definition_original: A Power Transmission Artifact that is designed to vary the output speed and torque in a rotating power transfer system.
definition_enriched: Vehicle Transmission is a Power Transmission Artifact that is designed to vary the output speed and torque in a rotating power transfer system.

label: Ventilation Control Artifact Function
definition_original: An Artifact Function that is realized in processes in which some Artifact is used to control the quality of air in some space.
definition_enriched: Ventilation Control Artifact Function is an Artifact Function that is realized in processes in which some Artifact is used to control the quality of air in some space.

label: Very High Frequency Communication Instrument
definition_original: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to participate in some process that has process part some Very High Frequency.
definition_enriched: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to transmit and/or receive radio signals in the very high frequency (VHF) band.

label: Video Camera
definition_original: A Camera that is designed to form and digitally or physically record a continuous stream of subsequent images of an entity or scene such that the images can be played back in succession as a video.
definition_enriched: Video Camera is a Camera that is designed to form and digitally or physically record a continuous stream of subsequent images of an entity or scene such that the images can be played back in succession as a video.

label: Visual Prosthesis
definition_original: An Artificial Eye that is designed to replace a missing eye, which performs the function of an eye.
definition_enriched: Visual Prosthesis is an Artificial Eye that is designed to replace a missing eye, which performs the function of an eye.

label: Voltage Regulating Artifact Function
definition_original: An Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to cause a change in the voltage magnitude between the sending and receiving end of an electrical component.
definition_enriched: Voltage Regulating Artifact Function is an Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to cause a change in the voltage magnitude between the sending and receiving end of an electrical component.

label: Waste Management Artifact Function
definition_original: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes of collecting, transporting, processing, recycling, monitoring, or disposing of waste materials.
definition_enriched: Waste Management Artifact Function is a Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes of collecting, transporting, processing, recycling, monitoring, or disposing of waste materials.

label: Water Transportation Artifact
definition_original: A Transportation Artifact that facilitates the movement of Agents and Vehicles via water.
definition_enriched: Water Transportation Artifact is a Transportation Artifact that facilitates the movement of Agents and Vehicles via water.

label: Watercraft
definition_original: A Vehicle that is designed to convey passengers, cargo, or equipment from one location to another by water travel.
definition_enriched: Watercraft is a Vehicle that is designed to convey passengers, cargo, or equipment from one location to another by water travel.

label: Weapon
definition_original: A Material Artifact that is designed to destroy or inflict damage to structures or systems, or to kill or wound living things by creating specific lethal or nonlethal effects.
definition_enriched: Weapon is a Material Artifact that is designed to destroy or inflict damage to structures or systems, or to kill or wound living things by creating specific lethal or nonlethal effects.

label: Wetting Agent Artifact Function
definition_original: A Surfactant Artifact Function that is realized in a process that reduces the water repellent tendency of a substance thereby allowing it to become wet.
definition_enriched: Wetting Agent Artifact Function is a Surfactant Artifact Function that is realized in a process that reduces the water repellent tendency of a substance thereby allowing it to become wet.

label: Wire Antenna
definition_original: A Radio Antenna that consists primarily of a length of wire.
definition_enriched: Wire Antenna is a Radio Antenna that consists primarily of a length of wire.

label: Wire Receiver
definition_original: A Radio Receiver that uses a Wire Antenna to intercept radio signals.
definition_enriched: Wire Receiver is a Radio Receiver that uses a Wire Antenna to intercept radio signals.

label: Wired Communication Artifact Function
definition_original: A Communication Artifact Function that is realized in a process that conveys meaningful signs by means of a (usually cylindrical) flexible strand or rod of metal.
definition_enriched: A Communication Artifact Function that is realized in a process that conveys meaningful signs via physical wired media, such as metallic conductors or optical fiber.

label: Wired Communication Reception Artifact Function
definition_original: A Communication Reception Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact receives information transmitted from another Artifact, where the transmission of information occurs via a direct connection using an electrical conductor.
definition_enriched: Wired Communication Reception Artifact Function is a Communication Reception Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact receives information transmitted from another Artifact, where the transmission of information occurs via a direct connection using an electrical conductor.

label: Wired Communication Relay Artifact Function
definition_original: A Communication Relay Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to first receive and then transmit information by means of wires from one Artifact to another for the purpose of communiction.
definition_enriched: Wired Communication Relay Artifact Function is a Communication Relay Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to first receive and then transmit information by means of wires from one Artifact to another for the purpose of communiction.

label: Wireless Telecommunication Network
definition_original: A Telecommunication Network that uses wireless connections to connect Telecommunication Network Nodes.
definition_enriched: Wireless Telecommunication Network is a Telecommunication Network that uses wireless connections to connect Telecommunication Network Nodes.

label: X-ray Microscope
definition_original: A Microscope that is designed to use Electromagnetic Radiation in the soft X-ray band to produce a significantly enlarged image of the Object.
definition_enriched: X-ray Microscope is a Microscope that is designed to use Electromagnetic Radiation in the soft X-ray band to produce a significantly enlarged image of the Object.

label: X-ray Telescope
definition_original: A Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing X-rays to form an enhanced image of the Object.
definition_enriched: X-ray Telescope is a Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing X-rays to form an enhanced image of the Object.
